  55. ‌let unsigned_to_int =
  56.   match Sys.word_size with
  57.   | 32 ->
  58.       let max_int = of_int Stdlib.max_int in
  59.       fun n ->
  60.         if compare zero n <= 0 && compare n max_int <= 0 then
  61.           Some (to_int n)
  62.         else
  63.           None
  64.   | 64 ->
  65.       (* So that it compiles in 32-bit *)
  66. ‌      let mask = 0xFFFF lsl 16 lor 0xFFFF in
  67.       fun n -> Some (to_int n land mask)
  68.   | _ ->
  69.       assert false

  86. ‌let unsigned_compare n m =
  87.   compare (sub n min_int) (sub m min_int)

  89. ‌let min x y : t = if x <= y then x else y

  92. (* Unsigned division from signed division of the same
  93.    bitness. See Warren Jr., Henry S. (2013). Hacker's Delight (2 ed.), Sec 9-3.
  94. *)
  95. ‌let unsigned_div n d =
  96.   if d < zero then
  97.     if unsigned_compare n d < 0 then zero else one
  98.   else
  99.     let q = shift_left (div (shift_right_logical n 1) d) 1 in
  100.     let r = sub n (mul q d) in
  101.     if unsigned_compare r d >= 0 then succ q else q

  103. ‌let unsigned_rem n d =
  104.   sub n (mul (unsigned_div n d) d)
